            <h2>Ranchlands Real Estate Market News</h2>
            <p>Ranchlands was formerly a hunting field for aboriginals and pastureland for European settlers before becoming a real estate market. Calgary acquired the region in 1961, and it became a neighbourhood in 1977. The park in Ranchlands has a glacial rubbing stone, known as "erratic" by geologists, to remember its historical significance.</p>
