                <div>
                    <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Parks &mdash;</h3>
                    <p>Ranchlands residents enjoy access to a wide range of recreational possibilities. The Crowfoot YMCA, as well as Crowfoot Arena, are only a short distance away. Tennis facilities, an outdoor skating rink, sports fields, and the Dan Scott Dance Studio, are all located inside the community. On the Northside, the town is bordered by a magnificent nature reserve with walking paths known as the Hawkwood Uplands Fitness Trail. </p>
                    <p>When it comes to relaxing at a park, Ranchlands residents have a variety of options. There's the Ranchlands Community Park which spans 12 acres, as well as Nose Hill Park, which has a variety of athletic and recreational facilities. </p>
                    <p>There are also a few smaller parks strewn across the neighbourhood. Playgrounds, sports fields, an outdoor skating rink, and tennis courts are also available in these smaller parks. </p>
                    <p>It may seem like the community is only home to parks and playgrounds. Don't be fooled by the name of the community, though. You can find some of the most modern amenities in the community, including incomparable shopping experiences.</p>
                    <p>Some amenities you can enjoy around Ranchlands other than parks and playgrounds include:</p>
                    <ul>
                        <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">Participating in the Ranchlands Community Association programmes that are very popular among residents.</li>
                        <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">Ranchlands residents can access over 240 services and amenities at Crowfoot Crossing, one of Calgary's largest outdoor malls. </li>
                        <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">Many dining, shopping, and entertainment options are available at Crowfoot Crossing, including Chapters Books, Home Depot, Calgary Coop & Safeway, Cineplex Odeon Theatres, and a variety of boutiques and large box businesses.</li>
                        <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">A basketball court, playground, as well as both hockey and recreational skating rinks are available in the community centre. </li>
                        <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">Scouts, Beavers, Girl Guides, and Sparks are some of the community's clubs. </li>
                        <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">The community's senior organization, New Horizons, meets once a week in the community centre.</li>
                    </ul>
                </div>
            </div>
        </div>
