        <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Demographics</h3>
            <p>Ranchlands was founded in 1977 after the region was acquired by the City of Calgary in 1961.</p>
            <p>Ranchlands had a total of 7,626 people living in 3,051 homes in the 2012 municipal census, up 1.3% from its 2011 demographic of 7,529. In 2012, it had a population size of 3,320/km2 (8,590/sq mi) on a surface area of 2.3 km2 (0.89 sq mi).</p>
            <p>The community's median age is 36.4 years, while the median age for the rest of Calgary is 37.4 years. Royal Oak has an average of 2.6 persons per family and a near-equal gender ratio of 50% female and 49% male residents.</p>
        </div>
        <div style="margin-top: 50px;">
            <h3 style="margin-bottom: 0;">Housing</h3>
            <p>Around 70% of the residents in this neighbourhood are homeowners, with the remaining being renters. The major housing types in this area of the city are single-family detached homes and townhouses.</p>
            <p>The most recent construction boom in this neighbourhood occurred between 1960 and 1980, hence the majority of the available homes date from this time.</p>
        </div>
