        <h2>FAQs about Ranchlands Real Estate and Neighborhood</h2>
        <ol>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
                <h3>What services does the community association offer?</h3>
                <p>The community association features a playground, a basketball court, and both hockey and recreational skating rinks. Scouts, Beavers, Girl Guides, and Sparks are some of the community programs. Meanwhile, the seniors club, The New Horizons, meets once a week at the community hall.</p>
            </li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
                <h3>How do I get around?</h3>
                <p>Calgary Transit routes 97,113, and 76 serve the Ranchlands community. Commuters also have access to the Crowfoot LRT and Crowfoot Trail for easy everyday transport.</p>
            </li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
                <h3>What's the best nearby restaurant?</h3>
                <p>The neighbourhood is home to several great restaurants. Residents love places such as Al's Pizza & Steakhouse, Fusion Sushi Ranchlands, and Stavros Pizza & Sports Bar.</p>
            </li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
                <h3>What are the people like in this community?</h3>
                <p>Ranchlands is and has always been a family-oriented community. The residents in this community are friendly and welcoming. They love spending time in nature and participate actively in the activities and programmes offered by the community association.</p>
            </li>
            <li style="margin-bottom: 3rem;">
                <h3>Are there any nearby gyms?</h3>
                <p>Crossfit Calgary is a fitness centre that's only 5 minutes away from the community on foot. Crowfoot Crossings also has the Melcor YMCA and they offer fitness classes, swimming, and hot tubs to members looking to stay active.</p>
            </li>

